    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense. So basically, if I frame it as the 'slippery slope' argument, I can argue that any attempt by the state to police 'truth' is just a move toward censorship. Do you think that's a solid enough foundation for the whole piece, or is that position generally viewed as too extreme to be taken seriously in political science?",
